description: Perhaps the tightest band in existence right now return with an astonishing new album - their first in 8 years - we ain’t talking about the Swedish psych troupe, nor the Greek metal act; but the infinitely superior Japanese goat (jp) who take the micro-precision of computer music and play it on instruments. description:
KILLER late 80’s digital business from Jazzbo riding an update on the MPLA rhythm, originally issued on his iconic Ujama imprint around the same era as that incredible ‘Replay Version’ reissued by Basic Channel’s Basic Replay label in 2007.

“One of the best 45s to come out of this late 80s digital era, no doubt." say the liner notes and it ain’t no lie -  if you like it on a digital/casio tip it really doesn’t get any colder than this, all sick vocal bumps on the A and that mad production and panned hi-hats... more
